                        <interp inst="t18410823-name-1119" type="given" value="WILLIAM"></interp>
                        <join result="offenceVictim" targOrder="Y" targets="t18410823-2182-offence-1 t18410823-name-1119"></join>William Rubergall</persName>, his master.</rs>
               </p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18410823-name-1120" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18410823-name-1120" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18410823-name-1120" type="surname" value="RUBERGALL"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18410823-name-1120" type="given" value="WILLIAM"></interp>WILLIAM RUBERGALL</persName>
                  </hi>. I live by the water-works at Pimlico. The prisoner was in my employ as carter—this wheelbarrow was taken out of</p>
               <xptr type="pageFacsimile" doc="184108230145"></xptr>
               <p>my yard—I went last week, and identified it at Mr. Davls's yard—when I gave the prisoner in charge he said he did not do it.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">Cross-examined by</hi> 
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">MR. CHAMBERS</hi>. <hi rend="italic">Q.</hi> How long had he left your service? <hi rend="italic">A.</hi> Five or six weeks after I discharged him I found the barrow—I had no Quarrel with him—he used to collect dung for me—this barrow is worth 3<hi rend="italic">s</hi>. now—I lost it twelve months ago—it was then worth 10<hi rend="italic">s</hi>.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18410823-name-1121" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18410823-name-1121" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18410823-name-1121" type="surname" value="DAVIKS"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18410823-name-1121" type="given" value="THOMAS"></interp>THOMAS DAVIKS</persName>
                  </hi>. I am a cow-keeper. This barrow was found on my premises—the prisoner used to wheel my dung out—he said he had an old barrow at home, which was broken, and if I would put it in repair, be would sell it me—I said, "Let me see it"—I gave him half-a-crown for it, and repaired it.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">Cross-examined. Q.</hi> You did a great deal to it? <hi rend="italic">A.</hi> Yes—it was done in my yard—another man, who worked for me, fetched the barrow.</p>
               <p>
